website_summaries.verdict: A versatile pressure washer with many features that you might expect on a higher priced unit.
pros: This slightly smaller model is capable of delivering 3,200 psi and 2.7 gpm
It features a Power Dial to quickly set the appropriate pressure and a 25-foot high-pressure hose
The unit also has an on-board cleaning tank and 4 quick-change nozzle tips
cons: The location, design, and build quality of the cleaning tank could benefit from a little upgrade

customer_reviews.title: Very disappointed in the quality of the power washer
customer_reviews.text: Very disappointed in the quality of the power washer, holster-very poorly designed and very cheap plastic. The hose holder is extremely cheap, it is a preformed piece of 1/8i sh wire. The on/off switch is terribly located on the side of the engine and poorly designed. The nozzles are made from lightweight plastic and lowquality metal, I found WEN nozzles to be a better grade overall-the engineering team gets and F.
customer_reviews.author: Dan Onishuk

customer_reviews.title: Wont stay running
customer_reviews.text: I was excited to get it and when I tried it, it would stay running. I was gonna return it but there was no return window. Only technical support I am 60 years old and I do go to start it. It was suppose to be easy start one time start, and if they help me I wouldn't be able to repair it on my own. I wish I would of went with the Honda Engine that never fells me.
customer_reviews.author: rose

customer_reviews.title: Very pleased with it's use and storage
customer_reviews.text: A very good price. The pressure is more than adequate for spraying concrete, fences and washing dirt bikes. I really like the soap reservoir which is easy to activate via a tube from reservoir to the pump and holds quite a bit of soap. Switching tips is a downer as a previous unit I used for years had a spray wand that included swival types on the end of the wand itself...a small complaint. The equipment is easy to start and very mobile with a very sizable fuel tank and soap reservoir. Hose storage on the back works well and is snap to put up for storage.
customer_reviews.author: James Rainwater

customer_reviews.title: Brand new Generac...
customer_reviews.text: Started it for the first time, ran really rough, wouldn't stop smoking. It ran rough like that for about 15 minutes then just died. Called Generac, some young girl who didn't know jack...started asking really dumb questions, which I suppose were on her computer trouble shooting screen. I asked for a dealer in our area, she gave me a number of some guy on the other side of the state, then asked her again if there was one closer, she then gave us one only a couple miles away...LOL We paid over 400.00 for this power washer from Amazon...no one can help us. This is really sad.
customer_reviews.author: Maint

customer_reviews.title: Worst Product Ever!
customer_reviews.text: We ordered this pressure washer as it was highly recommended. We used it for two days (less than 10 hours of use) and pressure was lost, and the water simply dribbled out. We have tried to contact Generac but have had no response. I believe we should be entitled to a refund or a new pressure washer. Don't bother ordering anything from Generac. I had to give it one star so that my review would show up. Otherwise, no stars!!
customer_reviews.author: Donna Marshall

customer_reviews.title: This power washer works great but I am giving it a 3 star solely ...
customer_reviews.text: This power washer works great but I am giving it a 3 star solely on the fact that the hose does not have any protection from the exhaust. It started to get tedious when I was using it and trying to keep the hose away from the exhaust. It also needs a better hook or holder for the hose.
customer_reviews.author: Amanda J. Tipton

customer_reviews.title: Five Stars
customer_reviews.text: After 13 months and 4-5 uses the engine went bad. No help from Amazon after calling 3 times and being hung up on; total of about an hour or more of my time. I was first told that they would refund or replace the unit on the first call that ultimately dropped, and later referred to Generac. I was given a $75 gift card for my inconvenience, but still out $359 for the power washer.
customer_reviews.author: John Matthew

customer_reviews.title: An this thing is amazing!!
customer_reviews.text: I bought this pressure washer back when it was still cold outside so haven't had time to try it out until now. An this thing is amazing!!! I absolutely love it. I use to have a Tory built 2,800 psi an this thing blow ls it out the water literally. All the attachments are easy an functionality is great. . Would definitely recommend this to anyone wanting to pressure wash anything from a car to a house. A deck to a boat. great!!!
customer_reviews.author: Chris cribb

customer_reviews.title: Good machine
customer_reviews.text: Have had this unit for over a month now and put many hours on it. Out of the box, was super easy to assemble and prepare for use. Works great, cranks easy, has been a sturdy setup. Only wish is to be able to remove the chemical container, because I either have to use up every bit of what's in it or have to tip the whole unit over to empty when I want to switch chemicals. Does not use gas as much gas as other units I have had. Generac has done well for me.

customer_reviews.title: Dead in 20 minutes
customer_reviews.text: It ran for 20 minutes and then died. I had to haul it 30 miles away to an authorized repair shop and am waiting to hear what is wrong with it. Update: rocker arm replaced and runs well now.

customer_reviews.title: Broken Switch right out of the box

customer_reviews.title: Excellent Power Washer

From my experience with stihl pressure washers I will certainly say this one is on par with them in a residential aspect. Very happy with my purchase, she runs like a champ..

product_meta.title: Generac 7019 OneWash 3,100 PSI, 2.4 GPM, Gas Powered Pressure Washer and PowerDial Gun
product_meta.description: Generac residential power washers give you cleaning power, reliability and-above all-ease of use in an affordable, compact unit you can use to clean everything from patio furniture to driveways and decks. The user-friendly design makes it easy to assemble, connect hoses, move almost effortlessly regardless of terrain, and clean longer and more comfortably.
feature_bullets: Ergonomic spray gun with integrated Power Dial allows you to easily adjust the pressure needed between four different tasks - car, wood, concrete and soap - at your fingertips
Powerful horizontal axial cam pump delivers 3100 PSI for tough cleaning
Convenient on-board 1/2 gallon detergent tank for hassle free cleaning
Generac 196cc OHV engine delivers maximum cleaning performance
25 foot high pressure hose connects to the rear of the spray gun for maximum convenience
